      "This week's JavaScript news â€” Read this e-mail on the Web\n\n\n\nJavaScript Weekly\n\nIssue 361 â€” November 17, 2017\n\n\n\nHow to Reduce the Cost of JavaScript\nAn increasing reliance on JS can result in needless performance issues for our users. Addy Osmani looks at how a little discipline can help.\n\nAddy Osmani\n\nHow Redux Works: A Counter-Example\nAn attempt to demystify Redux, a popular state container for JavaScript apps, with a â€˜backwards approachâ€™.\n\nDave Ceddia\n\nLuxon: A Chainable Wrapper for JavaScript Dates and Times\nFrom the creators of Moment.js, Luxon provides DateTime, Duration, and Interval types, as well as parsing and formatting for common formats.\n\nJS Foundation\n\nWant to ship better React Native apps faster? Meet App Center.\nFrom the creators of CodePush. Ship iOS and Android apps faster by connecting your appâ€™s repo and automating the rest. App Center builds your app in the cloud, tests it on real iOS devices, releases to beta testers, app stores or CodePush, and monitors with crash reports and analytics. Sign up now.\n\n\nMicrosoft\nÂ Â Sponsor\n\nCurrying Is Not Idiomatic in JavaScript\nThe good doctor explains \"why, in my opinion, currying is not a good fit for JavaScript.â€\n\n\nDr. Axel Rauschmayer\n\nGitHub Introduces Security Alerts for JS Projects\nItâ€™s possible to track your projectâ€™s dependencies directly in GitHub and if you do, GitHub can now notify you of vulnerabilities in them automatically.\n\nGitHub\n\nWebAssembly Support Now in All Major Browsers\nApple and Microsoft are shipping WebAssembly support in the latest versions of Safari and Edge so all 4 major browsers can now run code compiled to the wasm format.\n\nJudy DeMocker\n\nECharts: Powerful Charting and Visualization for the Browser\nBeen around a while but has grown a lot and now has extensions for major frameworks. Demos here.\n\n\nBaidu\n\nJobs \n\n\ncraigslist seeks JavaScript Developers (San Francisco, CA)CL seeks JS developers to join our small (~50) team. Come help us save the world, or at least our corner of the Internet.Â craigslist\n\n\nWeb Client EngineerJoin a growing engineering team that builds highly performant video apps across Web, iOS, Android, FireTV, Roku, tvOS, Xbox and more.Â Discovery Digital Media\n\n\nWant a New JavaScript Job Before the New Year?Try Underdog.io, where hundreds of the best tech companies go to find JavaScript talent. Companies email you directly as soon as next Monday.Â Underdog.io\n\n\nCan't find the right job? Want companies to apply to you? Try Hired.com.-->In Brief\nVueConf US 2018: March 26â€“28, 2018 in New Orleans, USAÂ news The VueConf.US 2018 call for proposals is now open, and closes December 1.VueConf US\nA Brief Introduction to Symbols, Generators and StreamsÂ tutorialRubens Pinheiro GonÃ§alves Cavalcante\nLearn and Understand JavaScriptâ€™s Reduce FunctionÂ tutorial Or Array.prototype.reduce(), more specifically.Brandon Morelli\nBuilding a NodeJS App with MongoDB Atlas and AWS ECS (Part 1)Â tutorial It's that time of year again. This is the first post in our annual \"Road to AWS re:Invent\" blog series.mongodbÂ Â Sponsor\nEasy ES6 Goodies for Busy JavaScript DevelopersÂ tutorial â€œa good basic introduction to three of the most useful ES6 goodiesâ€Michelle Gienow\nBuild a Server-Side Rendered Vue App with Nuxt.jsÂ tutorialChimezie Enyinnaya\nDeveloping a Chrome Extension using Angular 4Â tutorialJakub Kaczmarek\nStart Using Babel 7 Beta Today: What's New and HowÂ tutorialJeff Dolle\nWeb Workers Can Be ES6 Modules TooÂ tutorial OK, Chrome doesnâ€™t support it yet, but work is underway.Jeff Schiller\nCircleCI 2.0 Language Guide: JavaScriptÂ tutorial New to CircleCI 2.0? Read our JavaScript Language Guide for a detailed explanation of our configuration.CircleCIÂ Â Sponsor\nAngular Productivity Tips for WebStorm IDE UsersÂ tutorialJurgen Van de Moere\nBrowser Automation Revisited: Meet PuppeteerÂ tutorial node Puppeteer is a Node library that provides an API to control headless Chrome.Gergely Nemeth\nRecover Gracefully with React 16 Error BoundariesÂ tutorialROLLBARÂ Â Sponsor\nConverting 600k Lines to TypeScript in 72 HoursÂ story Specifically, from Google Closure-annotated JS.Lucidchart\nHow GitLab Uses Vue: One Year LaterÂ storyJacob Schatz\nHigh Performance JS in V8: How V8 Is Faster Than EverÂ video A 20 minute tour of V8â€™s latest code-generation architecture.Peter Marshall\nNeutronium: Build .NET Desktop Apps using HTML, CSS and JavaScriptÂ toolsNeutronium\nreact-scroll-to: Scroll to Position in ReactÂ codeDylan Paulus\nremoteStorage.js 1.0.0: Local Data Storage with Remote SyncingÂ code A project thatâ€™s as old as this newsletter.\nbent: Functional HTTP Client for Node with async/await SupportÂ code nodeMikeal Rogers\n\n\nCurated by Peter Cooper and published by Cooperpress.\nLike this? You may also enjoy: FrontEnd Focus : Node Weekly : React Status\nStop getting JavaScript Weekly : Change email address : Read this issue on the Web\nÂ© Cooperpress Ltd. Fairfield Enterprise Centre, Lincoln Way, Louth, LN11 0LS, UK",
